    The UltrasonicLocalization class implements the ultrasonic localization techniques using falling edge. Also implements movement to the point (1,1) using ultrasonic sensor

    • Method Detail

      • doLocalization

        public void doLocalization()
        Performs localization process based on falling edge technique, localizes the heading to 0 degrees. Uses the ultrasonice sensor to detect the edges of the wall and uses odometer theta values to calculate angle to turn to in order to localize heading to 0 degrees.

      • recordDistances

        public double[] recordDistances()
        Uses the ultrasonic sensor to read the x and y distances that the robot is from the wall. These distances are used to calculate the distance that the robot needs to travel to get to (1,1).
        Returns:
        double array containing x and y distances from the wall

      • usNavigate

        public void usNavigate​(double distX,
                       double distY)
        Moves the robot by the input distances distX, distY.
        Parameters:
        distX - The distance to move in the x direction
        distY - The distance to move in the y direction
